{:suite/id       :suites/spe-regression
 :suite/title    "SPE Regression — bounded-public-state-epsilon-SPE vocabulary and coverage"
 :suite/purpose  "Regression suite for Phase F–M SPE validation improvements. Covers the bounded-public-state-epsilon-spe equilibrium concept, subgame boundary classification (proper-subgame vs information-set-node), and the rich SPE result vocabulary (:spe/pass, :spe/epsilon-pass, :spe/fail-profitable-deviation, :spe/not-a-proper-subgame, :spe/inconclusive-*). v1 and v5: known-stable (pass). v2: inconclusive (buyer release, no dispute raised; no proper subgames). v3: pass (mixed-node trace — buyer raise_dispute is information-set, resolver execute_resolution is proper-subgame; no regret). v4: known-fail (theory-falsification; resolver slashed after verdict). v6: backward-induction mode — same two-node honest trace, bounded-backward-induction-spe concept. v7: reputation-spe — resolver stake top-up masks slash from bounded-spe (pass), but resolver-reputation-spe detects violation via slash-total (fail). v8: profile-matrix — same stake-top-up trace; resolver-reputation-profile-matrix concept; :reputation/none=pass (attacker indifferent), :reputation/conservative and :reputation/baseline=fail (any non-zero penalty deters)."
 :suite/prevents "Regressions in Phase F–M SPE additions: subgame boundary misclassification, incorrect SPE result vocabulary, missing counterexample traces, broken bounded-public-state-epsilon-spe concept dispatch."
